<HEADLINE>
FT  09 DEC 94 / World Commodities Prices: Wool
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Wool prices in the main international primary markets continue to fluctuate
narrowly. Finer merinos which eased just recently were unchanged or a
fraction dearer at this week's closing auctions in Australia, and prices for
middle range merino fleece have remained firm. The market indicator closed
down again on the week, at 768c/kg compared with 774c/kg, but the mid-week
quotation was 763c/kg. New Zealand crossbred prices eased more definitely,
with the indicator down 18 cents to 521c/kg. The overall impression is one
of a fairly firm market passing through a period of uncertainty. In the UK
sentiment has not been helped by the latest interest rate rise, which is
likely to depress consumer confidence further in an already fragile
situation.
</TEXT>
