<HEADLINE>
FT  09 DEC 94 / UK Company News: Trident steps up its Lloyd's involvement
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RALPH ATKINS, Insurance Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Trident, a Bermuda-based company investing in insurance and reinsurance, has
increased its involvement in Lloyd's of London by providing funds for a new
company investing in syndicates run by Venton managing agencies.
Trident was formed a year ago by Marsh McLennan, the world's largest
insurance broker, J P Morgan, Mid Ocean, a Bermuda reinsurance company, and
Byrne Sons, a small investment bank.
Venton has raised a total of Pounds 18.5m in corporate capital to invest in
three insurance syndicates via two vehicles, one capitalised exclusively by
Trident. Venton has not disclosed how much Trident, which is also connected
with the Hiscox managing agencies, has invested.
</TEXT>
