FT  09 DEC 94 / Letters to the Editor: Airline puff
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   From ANDREW SMITH
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Sir, Your survey of business travel ('When smoke gets in passengers' eyes',
December 5) contained a small error concerning smoking on aircraft. While in
the Middle East recently, I was pleasantly surprised to find that Gulf Air
has a no-smoking policy on all intra-Gulf flights  - a great relief after
earlier trips in the region where, as you say, some airlines have smoking on
the right, no-smoking on the left.
Andrew Smith,
11a Bronsart Road,
London SW6 6AJ
