FT  09 DEC 94 / TUC plea over deaths at work
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A new offence of 'manslaughter at work' should be created to target
negligent company executives responsible for workplace safety, the TUC urged
today.
More than 400 people die at work every year due to poor safety standards but
manslaughter charges are rare even when unions prove that an employer is
negligent, said the TUC.
Mr John Monks, TUC general secretary, said: 'Prison should be the final
deterrent to careless, recalcitrant employers who cut corners for a quick
profit.'
