<HEADLINE>
FT  08 DEC 94 / International Capital Markets: Dual-currency Pounds 300m
facility for Britannia BS - Syndicated loans
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By MARTIN BRICE
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Britannia Building Society has asked Westdeutsche Landesbank to arrange
a Pounds 300m dual-currency revolving loan with multiple maturities.
The loan, which has a swingline option, has a commitment fee of 8 basis
points over the London interbank offered rate (Libor) for the first four
years and a day, rising to 8.25 basis points up to five years and 8.5 basis
points for the sixth year.
The margin fee is 18 basis points for the first four years and a day, 20
basis points for year five and 22 basis points for year six. Participation
fees are 5.5 basis points for Pounds 10m, 7 basis points for Pounds 15m and
8.5 basis points for Pounds 20m or more.
A presentation was made on Monday and banks have until December 19 to join
the syndicate. A banker close to the deal said there had been a good initial
response and the loan should be signed in early January.
A Dollars 700m revolving credit for Svenska Cellulosa, one of Europe's
largest paper companies, arranged by Chemical Bank and Handelsbanken
Markets, has been signed.
The loan was oversubscribed in general syndication and increased from
Dollars 500m. A total of 31 banks joined the syndicate.
A Pounds 120m revolving credit for General Utilities, the holding company
for the UK water company assets of Compagnie Generale des Eaux of France,
has been increased to Pounds 126m after being oversubscribed in syndication.
A total of nine banks joined the syndicate.
A Pounds 237.5m revolving loan for MAI Finance, the international financial
services and media company, has been signed. It was increased by Pounds
37.5m in syndication. Chemical Bank was the arranger and a further 12 banks
joined the syndicate.
</TEXT>
