FT  08 DEC 94 / Observer: Empowered?
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Fed up with journalists, market researchers, publishers and other
undesirables badgering you? Why not take a leaf out of the book of
octogenarian management guru Peter Drucker, who replies to correspondents
(including the FT) with a pre-printed message that caters for most
eventualities. Drucker 'greatly appreciates your kind interest, but is
unable to: contribute articles or forewords; comment on manuscripts or
books; take part in panels and symposia; join committees or boards of any
kind; answer questionnaires; give interviews; and appear on radio or
television'.
