FT  08 DEC 94 / Observer: Cheeky one
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Has prominent Budapest stockbroker Csaba von Csiky lost his shirt in the
market? Sharp-eyed delegates to the Budapest gathering of the CSCE this week
would have noticed von Csiky flashing an identity pass describing himself as
a 'janitor' at the Hotel Kempinski.
As far as Observer is aware his finances are in perfect order, but he has
had a spot of bother of a different kind. For the duration of the
conference, Hungarian police had ordered that no one could stay or enter the
Kempinski - normally a salubrious enough pad - or any of the city's top
hotels, for that matter, unless part of an official delegation, or a member
of staff.
It didn't matter one jot to the police that von Csiky is actually a resident
at the Kempinski. He was told he had to move elsewhere.
Consequently, the embarrassed hotel management found the only way it could
outwit Hungary's notorious ex-communist bureaucracy was by putting von Csiky
on its staff.
